			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I have a little bit of information that I think might help.  I don't think anyone's posted this yet.<BR>
<BR>
When you speak with Kane Bayle (in the Bloodsabers guild) and say either, &quot;I am a Bloodsaber.&quot; or &quot;The disease is spreading.&quot; he will give you Blackburrow Stout.  I can't remember which phrase you say, but it's definately one of those two.  <BR>
He tells you to bring the Stout to Barn Bloodstone in Highhold Pass.<BR>
When you give Barn the stout, he gives you &quot;Bayle List I&quot; and tells you to go speak with &quot;a woman called Opal&quot; in Freeport.<BR>
He says that he &quot;hears she works with the Arcane Scientists.&quot;  You are to tell her that &quot;The disease is spreading.&quot;<BR>
I haven't done that part of the quest yet, but I'll make a wild guess that she gives you &quot;Bayle List II.&quot;<BR>
<BR>
I know from killing Dyllin Starshine in Highhold Pass (for the Testament of Vanear quest) you get &quot;Bayle List III&quot; but I suspect there is a peaceful way to get it from him (probably say &quot;The disease is spreading.&quot;) because killing him lowers faction with the Bloodsabers.<BR>
<BR>
Another thing to note is that Barn warns you not to return to Kane Bayle without all three lists.<BR>
<BR>
Erasmis Nightbringer<BR>
High Priest of Bertoxxulous, 33rd Order<BR>
Rodcet Nife
				</font>
